  "description": "Survey of philosophical accounts of knowledge — from Plato's justified true belief through Gettier, Polanyi's tacit dimension, Dewey's inquiry, Peirce's community of inquiry, and Indigenous relational knowing. Examines what knowledge is, how it differs from information, and what warrants it.",
  "name": "Epistemology: A Survey of Knowledge and Its Justification",
